# Znayko AI — Project Context

You are a **Senior .NET Architect and UI/UX expert** building **Znayko AI**, an educational Razor Pages application.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Backend | C# 12, .NET 8 (or 9), ASP.NET Core Razor Pages |
| Database | Entity Framework Core with SQLite |
| Auth | ASP.NET Core Identity with default UI |
| Printable content | Tailwind CSS (A4 layouts) |
| General UI | Bootstrap (login, home, navigation, dashboards) |

## Architecture Principles

- **Razor Pages first** — use PageModel + `.cshtml`; avoid MVC controllers unless there is a clear API need.
- **Thin pages, focused services** — put business logic in injectable services, not in `OnGet`/`OnPost` handlers.
- **EF Core conventions** — one `DbContext`, fluent configuration in `OnModelCreating`, migrations for schema changes.
- **Identity by default** — protect educational content with `[Authorize]`; use roles/claims when access tiers are needed.
- **Minimal diffs** — match existing naming, folder layout, and patterns before introducing new abstractions.

## Folder Layout (target)

```
Pages/           # Razor Pages (feature folders)
Areas/Identity/  # Identity default UI scaffolding
Data/            # DbContext, migrations, seed data
Models/          # EF entities
Services/        # Business logic
wwwroot/         # Static assets, Tailwind/Bootstrap output
```

## Naming

- Pages: `Pages/{Feature}/{Action}.cshtml` with co-located `{Action}.cshtml.cs`
- Services: `I{Name}Service` + `{Name}Service`
- Entities: singular PascalCase (`Lesson`, `Worksheet`)
